##### I first started honing my design skills during my junior year of high school. I started with using Procreate and then started learning Photoshop and InDesign in my career-building school. During the second year of that school, I learned Illustrator and fell in love with that program. I went to the University of Hartford during my freshman year of college. I created mostly traditional works during my time there. I learned how to use charcoal, acrylic paint (in different ways), pen & ink, and much more. While at SUNY New Paltz, I took many Graphic Design classes that have pushed me further than I imagined I would go as a designer. In the rest of my years there, I can only hope to learn more.
{% /CustomCSSWrapper %}

